<section class="case-chapter" data-chapter="takeaway">
  <h2>Remember</h2>
  <div class="case-takeaway">
    <h3>Key takeaways</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <div class="tone-junior">REACT_APP_*, VITE_*, and NEXT_PUBLIC_* variables are baked into your JavaScript. They're public. Never put real secrets in them.</div>
        <div class="tone-mid">The proxy pattern is the fundamental fix: your frontend calls your backend, your backend calls the third-party API with the key — key never reaches the client.</div>
        <div class="tone-staff">Add Gitleaks or GitHub secret scanning to CI — catch keys before they ship. Treat any key committed to git or shipped in a bundle as permanently compromised.</div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <div class="tone-junior">Serverless functions (Vercel API routes, Netlify Functions) are the easiest proxy for static sites — no full backend needed.</div>
        <div class="tone-mid">In Next.js, use server-side data fetching (Server Components, getServerSideProps) — the API key is only used server-side and never serialized to the client.</div>
        <div class="tone-staff">Defense in depth: rotate leaked keys immediately, rate-limit proxy endpoints, and configure third-party APIs to allowlist only your server IP.</div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
